Cryptocurrencies are digital currencies which are encrypted to secure transaction.
It is different in its function as its control is decentralized, which eliminates the possibility of corruption.
It works through blockchain in the form of distributed ledgers.
Currently, there are more than 1500 cryptocurrencies
Out of these, Bitcoin, Tether and Etherum are mostly preferred by the beginners.
In india, Koinex, Unocoin and zeppay are the startups that allows trading of these blockchains. 
Crytocurrency is the next wave of opportunity in the world.
But It is still not a legal tender in India.
